description: Affinity Metals Corp. engages in the acquisition, exploration, and development of mineral properties in Canada. It explores for copper, gold, silver, lead, and zinc deposits. Its flagship property is the Regal property covering an area of approximately 8,800 hectares located in the prolific Kootenay Arc near Revelstoke, British Columbia. The company was formerly known as Acme Resources Inc. and changed its name to Affinity Metals Corp. in March 2017. Affinity Metals Corp. was incorporated in 1978 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Robert Nathan Edwards CPA, CGA, CPA
